def norm(data):
    """"""
    return (data - np.min(data)) / (np.max(data) - np.min(data))

def plot_ScatterMatrix_Heatmap(data, fig_pre_name, save=True):
    """
    :param data: 
    :param fig_pre_name: 
    :param save: 
    :return: None
        notebook 
    """
    # 
    fig = px.scatter_matrix(
        data, 
        title=fig_pre_name + '', 
    )
    if save:
        fig.write_image('./img/1-' + fig_pre_name + '.svg')
    fig.show()

    # 
    corrs = data.corr(method='pearson')  # 'pearson', 'kendall', 'spearman'
    figure = ff.create_annotated_heatmap(
        z=corrs.values,
        x=list(corrs.columns),
        y=list(corrs.index), 
        annotation_text=corrs.round(3).values, 
        showscale=True, 
        colorscale='reds', 
    )
    figure.update_layout(title=fig_pre_name + '')
    if save:
        figure.write_image('./img/1-' + fig_pre_name + '.svg')
    figure.show()
    return None

预测指标ABCD¶

4

MSE()R^2()

$$0.2(1 - Mape) + 0.8 * Accuracy_5$$

$Ape$()$$Ape = \frac{\left| \hat{y} - y\right|}{y}$$

$Mape$()$$Mape = \frac{1}{m} \sum\limits_{i=1}^{m}Ape_i$$

$Accuracy_5$($5 \%$)$$Accuracy_5 = \frac{count(Ape \le 0.05)}{count(total)}$$

th = 0.1  # n 
con = 0.2  # 

def run_model(model_name, model, X=X, Ys=Ys, index_num=index_num):
    """
    :param model_name:
    :param model:
    :param X:
    :param Ys:
    :param index_num:
    :return: [yhats]
         img 
    """
    data = []
    yhats = []
    print(model_name, ":\n")
    for i in range(index_num):
        Y = Ys.iloc[:, i]
        xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = train_test_split(np.array(X), 
                                                        np.array(Y), 
                                                        test_size=0.3, 
                                                        random_state=24, 
                                                        shuffle=True)
        
        model.fit(xtrain, ytrain)  # todo 
        yhat = model.predict(xtest)  # todo 
        yhats.append(yhat)

        acc = predict_accuracy(ytest, yhat, type=1, th=th, con=con)  # todo 
        print("accuracy:", acc)
        print("MSE:", MSE(yhat, ytest), "MAE:", MAE(yhat, ytest), end='')
        print("R2:", model.score(xtest, ytest))

        print("", model.predict(data_to_predict))# todo 
        
        # todo 
        Yhat = model.predict(X)
        data.append(go.Scatter(
            x=data_part1.iloc[:, 0], y=Y, 
            name=index_name[i] + "-", 
            line=dict(color=index_colors[i * 2 + 1], width=1.5)), 
        )
        data.append(go.Scatter(
            x=data_part1.iloc[:, 0], y=Yhat,
            name=index_name[i] + "-", 
            line=dict(color=index_colors[i * 2], width=1.5)), 
        )
        
        # todo 
        cols = str(Y.name)
        Yhat = pd.DataFrame(Yhat)
        Y.index = [i for i in range(len(Y))]
        Y_data = pd.concat([Y, Yhat], axis=1)
        Y_data.columns = ["", ""]
        
        Y_data.figure(
            kind='spread', 
            color=[index_colors[i * 2 + 1], index_colors[i * 2]], 
            title='' +  model_name + '' + cols + '', 
        ).write_image('./img/1-' +  model_name + '' + cols + '.svg')
        Y_data.iplot(
            kind='spread', 
            color=[index_colors[i * 2], index_colors[i * 2 + 1]], 
            title='' +  model_name + '' + cols + '', 
        )
        print()
    fig = go.Figure(data=data, )
    
    annotations = []
    annotations.append(dict(
        x=0.5, y=-0.1,
        xref='paper', yref='paper', 
        xanchor='center', yanchor='top',
        text='',
        font=dict(size=16),
        showarrow=False, 
    ))
    fig.update_layout(
        title='' +  model_name + '',
        annotations=annotations,
        template="plotly_white",
    )
    fig.write_image('./img/1-' + model_name + '.svg')
    fig.show()
    return pd.DataFrame(yhats, index=index_name).T

hidden_num = [8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 64, 32, 16, 8, 4]
epoch = 1000
optimizer = 'adam'

def run_BP(X=X, Ys=Ys, index_num=index_num):
    data_to_predict = np.array(
        [[1404.89, 859.77, 52.75, 96.87, 46.61, 22.91, ],
         [1151.75, 859.77, 52.75, 96.87, 46.61, 22.91, ], 
        ],
    )
#     data_to_predict = np.array(
#         [[1404.89,859.77,52.75,96.87,46.61,22.91, ], 
#          [1151.75,859.77,52.75,96.87,46.61,22.91, ],
#          [1173.63, 813.92, 49.24, 90.38, 46.13, 28.16, ],
#          [854.55, 767.64, 49.24, 90.38, 46.13, 28.16, ], 
#         ], 
#     )  # pytorchbug
    data = []
    print("BP")
    for i in range(index_num):
        Y = Ys.iloc[:, i]
        xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = train_test_split(
            np.array(X, dtype=float), np.array(Y, dtype=float), 
            test_size=0.3,
            random_state=10, 
            shuffle=True,
        )
        bp = BP(
            X.shape[1], hidden_num, 1, 
            epoch=epoch, 
            optimizer=optimizer,
            normalization=True
        )
        bp.train(xtrain, ytrain)
        y_pre = bp.predict(xtest).cpu().detach().numpy()
        acc = predict_accuracy(ytest[:, None], y_pre, type=1)  # 
        print("accuracy:", acc)
        print("", bp.predict(data_to_predict))
#         print(mean_squared_error(y_true=ytest[:, None], y_pred=y_pre))
#         print("MSE:", MSE(yhat, ytest), "MAE:", MAE(yhat, ytest), end='')
#         print("R2:", model.score(xtest, ytest))

        # todo 
        Yhat = bp.predict(np.array(X, dtype=float)).cpu().detach().numpy()
        data.append(go.Scatter(
            x=data_part1.iloc[:, 0], y=Y,
            name=index_name[i] + "-",
            line=dict(color=index_colors[i * 2 + 1], width=1.5)), 
        )
        data.append(go.Scatter(
            x=data_part1.iloc[:, 0], y=np.squeeze(Yhat),
            name=index_name[i] + "-",
            line=dict(color=index_colors[i * 2], width=1.5)), 
        )

        # todo 
        cols = str(Y.name)
        Yhat = pd.DataFrame(Yhat)
        Y.index = [i for i in range(len(Y))]
        Y_data = pd.concat([Y, Yhat], axis=1)
        Y_data.columns = ["", ""]
        Y_data.figure(
            kind='spread',
            color=[index_colors[i * 2 + 1], index_colors[i * 2]],
            title='BP' + cols,
        ).write_image('./img/1-BP' + cols + '.svg')
        Y_data.iplot(
            kind='spread',
            color=[index_colors[i * 2 + 1], index_colors[i * 2]],
            title='BP' + cols,
        )
    fig = go.Figure(data=data)

    annotations = []
    annotations.append(dict(
        x=0.5, y=-0.1,
        xref='paper', yref='paper',
        xanchor='center', yanchor='top',
        text='',
        font=dict(size=16),
        showarrow=False,
    ))
    fig.update_layout(
        title='BP',
        annotations=annotations,
    )
    fig.write_image('./img/1-BP.svg')
    fig.show()
    return None
